HEADWORD: Ambulacral
<hw>Am`bu*la"cral</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to ambulacra; avenuelike; <as>as, the
<ex>ambulacral</ex> ossicles, plates, spines, and suckers of
echinoderms</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

